         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/6/87 ¶  ¶ I am aware, dear Mr Dyer, that many novelties occur among Mr Forbes Papuan plants, and I hope to work them out during the latter half of this year, when my “Key to the syst. of Vict. plan...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.06.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 224-5.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 8 Aug 1887 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and annotated by W. Thiselton-Dyer</seg>: Answered 10.8.87 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[letter not found].</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>28/6/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am aware, dear Mr Dyer, that many novelties occur among Mr Forbes Papuan plants, and I hope to work them out during the latter half of this year, when my “Key to the syst. of Vict. plants”<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.11.02.</p>
               </note> will be out, and thus my time be free again for the New Guinea Flora. From Mr Carruthers you will have learnt, that the elaboration of the <name key="Dicotyledoneae">Dicotyledoneae</name> is left to me (except <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name> &amp; <name key="Utriceae">Utriceae</name>.) Mr Ridley takes the <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name> and Mr Carruthers the ferns.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Carruthers, 1 March 1886; M to H. Ridley, 12 January 1887 (in this edition as 87-01-12d). </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As the R. Austr. geogr. Soc. voted for Forbes last tour on <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">my</hi>
               </seg> proposition somewhat reluctantly £500 - -, it would be but just that the elaboration of his plants, as far as just indicated, should be left to me. I am too far from Europe, to make further arrangements; moreover such overwhelming material is from other tropic regions in England, to be worked out, that the Papuan Flora, as Sir Joseph Hooker conceded already some years ago, should be left to me, as I was first in the field.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 25 March 1873; J. Hooker to M, 17 January 1884.</p>
               </note> My strenght and eyesight may last me perhaps only yet a short time, but so long as it does, no one will, I feel sure, grudge me the New Guinea work</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I believe, that I shall be able to congratulate you soon on some honors from Germany.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thiselton-Dyer was elected to the <seg style="">Academia Caesarea Leopoldino-Carolina Naturae Curiosorum in 1887 (List of members, </seg>
                     <ref target="http://www.leopoldina.org/en/members/members-since-1652/"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0000ff; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0000ff; ">
                           <seg style="">http://www.leopoldina.org/en/members/members-since-1652/</seg>
                        </seg>
                     </ref>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[accessed 6 December 2014]).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If Mr Forbes, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">as I recently have recommended</hi>
               </seg> gets means from the special Commissioner Mr Douglas, for further travels in N. Guinea out of the £15 000 voted by N.S.W. Vict. &amp; Queensl., then Mr Forbes will in honor be bound to render his collections accessible to the three colonies, which give him the means (and probably the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">only</hi>
               </seg> means) for continuing his researches. Any unfairness in this respect would likely be made not only a subject of discussions in the colonial press here, but also most likely in the three parliaments; which vote the fund for the High Commissioner.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See A. Todd (1894), pp. 248-53.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
